CONFIGURATIONS:
	COMMAND-LINE TOOLS:
	- install zsh (if not already installed)
		- create startup files
			- .zshrc
			- .zlogout
		- install oh-my-zsh
		- change the default shell to zsh
	- install vim
		- download vim-gtk[3] for clipboard support
		- install vim-plug plugin manager
	- install neofetch
	- install onefetch
	- install clang[-10 | -11]
	- install htop
	- install iotop
	- download media codecs for video support (if required)
	- install fd
	- install ripgrep
	- install tree
	- install diff-so-fancy
	- install fzf
	- install ttyper
		- need cargo package manager before installation
	- install bat
	- install dictd
		- installation instructions: {https://www.unixmen.com/look-dictionary-definitions-via-terminal/}
		- install dict-gcide, an english dictionary database
		- install dict-freedict-eng-hin, an english-to-hindi dictionary database
	- install build-essential
	- install gdb
	- install trans (translate-shell) {https://github.com/soimort/translate-shell}
		- required gawk
			- install gawk
	- install starship (a custimzable prompt for any shell)
	- install pip[3]
		- install pyWhat
	- install a git client
		- GitHub desktop
		- SmartGit
		- Sublime Merge
	- install prettyping
	- install tldr
	- install dbg-macro {https://github.com/sharkdp/dbg-macro}
	- install duf (optional)
	- install exa (optional)
		- need cargo package manager before installation

	GUIs:
	- install BleachBit (if required)
	- install spotify
	- install free download manager (optional, using wget tool instead)
	- install vlc
		- set vlc as default application
	- install discord (pending)
	- install vscode (optional)
	- install xournal (optional)

CHECK-OUT COMMAND-LINE TOOLS:
	- zsh shell
	- ack vim plugin
		- use it with ripgrep
	- fzf vim plugin
	- fzf ripgrep configurations

CHECK-OUT GUIs SOFTWARES:
	- Alacritty terminal
	- i3 tiling windows manager
